The first dataset is available at github.com/drisso/fletcher2017data.

We load the data.

We only care about transcription factor (TF) genes. We can retrieve a list from github.

tf <- read.table("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rufletch/p63-HBC-diff/master/ref/ATFDB_mm_TF.txt", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

genes <- intersect(rownames(fletcher), tf[,1])
length(genes)
## [1] 1100
datamat <- counts(fletcher)[genes,]

ZINB

library(zinbwave)
fit <- zinbFit(datamat)

## Mu
mu <- colMeans(getMu(fit))
summary(mu)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
##    0.0012   13.7805   39.8240   61.2111   69.9033 2438.5310
hist(mu, breaks=30)

which.max(mu)
## [1] 759
summary(datamat[759,])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##       0       4     202    2436    2280   51480
## Pi
pi <- colMeans(getPi(fit))
summary(pi)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
## 0.0000082 0.4245905 0.7237700 0.6387644 0.8911165 0.9984355
hist(pi, breaks=30)

## Theta
theta <- getTheta(fit)
unique(theta)
## [1] 0.246205

NB

fitnb <- zinbFit(datamat, zeroinflation = FALSE)

## Mu
mu <- colMeans(getMu(fitnb))
summary(mu)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
##    0.0011    0.9627    8.3140   36.8398   24.0669 2245.3251

## [1] 759

##       0       4     202    2436    2280   51480
## Theta
theta <- getTheta(fitnb)
unique(theta)
## [1] 0.07057055

Dataset 2

The second dataset is available in Dropbox.

We load the data.

data2 <- read.table("~/Dropbox (unipd)/zinb_graph/data/oe_data_10x_neuronal.txt")
data2 <- t(data2)

We only care about transcription factor (TF) genes. We can retrieve a list from github.

length(intersect(rownames(data2), tf[,1]))
## [1] 878
## random subset of 800 cells
set.seed(124)
idx <- sample(colnames(data2), 800)
data2 <- data2[,idx]

geneidx <- which(matrixStats::rowVars(data2)>0)
data2 <- data2[geneidx,]

ZINB

fit2 <- zinbFit(data2)

## Mu
mu <- colMeans(getMu(fit2))
summary(mu)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
##  0.001261  0.095457  0.263763  0.736624  0.653847 17.172270
hist(mu, breaks=30)

which.min(mu)
## [1] 419
summary(data2[419,])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## 0.00000 0.00000 0.00000 0.00125 0.00000 1.00000
## Pi
pi <- colMeans(getPi(fit2))
summary(pi)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
## 0.0001635 0.0253599 0.3346420 0.3632315 0.5995622 0.9982713
hist(pi, breaks=30)

## Theta
theta <- getTheta(fit2)
unique(theta)
## [1] 1.028065e+23

NB

fitnb2 <- zinbFit(data2, zeroinflation = FALSE)

## Mu
mu <- colMeans(getMu(fitnb2))
summary(mu)
##     Min.  1st Qu.   Median     Mean  3rd Qu.     Max. 
##  0.00125  0.05125  0.13250  0.48120  0.37312 15.93242
hist(mu, breaks=30)

## Theta
theta <- getTheta(fitnb2)
unique(theta)
## [1] 3.877963e+16
